Lecturer Thys Odendal says the structure of the 130-year-old performance hall was also damaged. CAPE TOWN As the Cape Peninsula University of Technology (CPUT) assesses the damage caused by an arson attack at its Goodnow Hall, concerns have been raised as to whether the damage will be repaired.Several paintings memorabilia and antique musical instruments were destroyed in last week s blaze as students mobilised to take their march for free education to parliament.Lecturer Thys Odendal says the structure of the 130-year-old performance hall was also damaged. The funds have to be found. Whether the university has the necessary insurance or whether we ve to go the route of contacting alumni and musicians around the country who started this hall. (Edited by Leeto M Khoza)